description: Nest API and accessibility QA steps must start with freeing port 3002 / killing stray processes.
alwaysApply: true
---

# QA / API — kill port first

Whenever you give **copy-paste steps** (or extend RUNBOOK-style docs) for:

- `npm run start:api`, `start:dev`, or any Nest listen on **3002**
- `npm run qa:accessibility:*` (runner expects API up)
- `npm run qa:bulk:run` (bulk core canvas QA runner; same API + QA headers)

**Always put this block first** (PowerShell, repo root), before starting the API or assuming port 3002 is free:

1. `npm run kill:api-port`
2. If still in use: `netstat -ano | findstr :3002` then `taskkill /PID <pid> /F`

Do not skip this unless the user explicitly says the port is already clear.

## Accessibility runner — one `qa:accessibility:run` per paste; build before fix-mode

- **Do not** put **two** `npm run qa:accessibility:run` lines in one copy-paste block. If they need scan-only **and** fix-mode, give **two separate** sections and put **`npm run qa:accessibility:build`** or **`npm run qa:accessibility:build:force`** **between** them (re-seed violations). Never imply “run A then run B” without that build in the middle.

- **Fix-mode** (`QA_FIX_AUTO=1`): always include **`npm run qa:accessibility:build:force`** (or `qa:accessibility:build`) **in the same flow immediately before** the single fix run, so the course still has seeded violations. Do **not** label that build “optional” for fix-mode.

- **Scan-only**: before it, `Remove-Item Env:QA_FIX_AUTO -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue` so the shell is not still in fix-mode.

- Do not tell the user to “pull/sync” when you can run `git pull` in the repo yourself.
